# Markdown documentation files
*.md
# Root *.md is ignored by default with a curated allowlist below.
# CLAUDE.md is the repo's engineering contract for agents and humans (it points
# at LOOPS.md); both are team documentation, not personal scratch, so they are
# allowlisted. Revert these two lines if the intent was to keep them local —
# note that CLAUDE.md must live at the repo root to be picked up automatically,
# so it cannot simply move under docs/.
#
# slop.md joins them for the same reason: CLAUDE.md now points at it as part of
# reviewing any UI change, so leaving it ignored would dangle that link for
# anyone cloning.
!CLAUDE.md
!LOOPS.md
!slop.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!DEV_GUIDE.md
!docs/**/*.md
# release-notes/ is the per-version human release note that `ship it` writes.
# Without this line `*.md` above swallows it AT ANY DEPTH and the notes are
# silently untracked — the whole point of them is that they ship.
!release-notes/**/*.md
!todo.md
!README.md
*.txt
components-list.txt
components-list.csv


vite.config.http.ts

